block content

  header.bg-primary.text-white.py-5(style="margin-top: 76px;")
    .container.px-4.px-lg-5
      .row.justify-content-center
        .col-lg-8
          nav(aria-label="breadcrumb")
            ol.breadcrumb.mb-3
              li.breadcrumb-item
                a.text-white-50(href="/") Home
              li.breadcrumb-item
                a.text-white-50(href="/blog.html") Blog
              li.breadcrumb-item.active.text-white(aria-current="page") MAT Facts
          h1.display-5.fw-bold Medication-Assisted Treatment (MAT) in Spokane: The Facts
          p.lead.mt-3.text-white-75 How science and medicine are changing the way we treat opioid and alcohol addiction in the Inland Northwest.
          .small.text-white-50.mt-2
            i.bi.bi-calendar3.me-1
            | March 2026 &nbsp;·&nbsp;
            i.bi.bi-clock.me-1
            | 7 min read

  section.page-section
    .container.px-4.px-lg-5
      .row.justify-content-center
        .col-lg-8

          p.lead.mt-5
            | For decades, addiction treatment was seen as "abstinence only." However, as the opioid epidemic (fentanyl and heroin) has devastated Spokane, medical professionals have increasingly turned to **Medication-Assisted Treatment (MAT)**. MAT is the use of FDA-approved medications in combination with counseling and behavioral therapies.

          hr.my-5

          h2.mt-4 
            i.bi.bi-capsule-pill.text-primary.me-2
            | Common Medications Used
          ul
            li
              strong Suboxone (Buprenorphine):
              |  Helps manage cravings and withdrawal symptoms for opioids without producing the "high" of heroin or fentanyl.
            li
              strong Methadone:
              |  A long-standing treatment for opioid addiction, typically dispensed daily in a clinic setting.
            li
              strong Vivitrol (Naltrexone):
              |  A monthly injection that blocks the effects of opioids and alcohol, significantly reducing the desire to use.

          h2.mt-5 
            i.bi.bi-check-lg.text-primary.me-2
            | Is it "Trading One Addiction for Another?"
          p
            | This is the most common myth. In addiction, a person is chasing a high and their life is unmanageable. In MAT, the medication stabilizes brain chemistry, allowing the person to work, care for their family, and participate in therapy. The goal of MAT is **recovery**, not intoxication.
          p
            | Research shows that MAT decreases opioid use, opioid-related overdose deaths, and criminal activity. In Spokane, it has been a literal lifesaver for thousands.

          h2.mt-5 
            i.bi.bi-geo-alt.text-primary.me-2
            | Where to find MAT in Spokane
          p
            | Many local clinics offer MAT, and most accept Apple Health (Medicaid).
          ul
            li
              strong Spokane Regional Health District (Treatment Services):
              |  Offers comprehensive OTP (Opioid Treatment Program) services including methadone.
            li
              strong Ideal Option:
              |  A specialized MAT provider with multiple locations across Spokane and the Valley.
            li
              strong CHAS Health:
              |  Integrates MAT into their general medical and behavioral health care.

          hr.my-5

          .card.border-0.shadow.text-center.p-5.mb-4(style="border-radius: 16px; background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0d6efd11 0%, #0d6efd22 100%);")
            i.bi.bi-clipboard-pulse.display-4.text-primary.mb-3
            h3.fw-bold Interested in MAT?
            p.text-muted.mb-4
              | We have a dedicated section of our directory for medical providers who offer Suboxone, Vivitrol, and other life-saving medications.
            .d-flex.flex-wrap.gap-3.justify-content-center
              a.btn.btn-primary.btn-lg(href="/medical-mental-health.html")
                i.bi.bi-search.me-2
                | View MAT Providers
